          <Comment>For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 280880). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with CLCN1-related conditions. This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency). This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Gln675Lysfs*119) in the CLCN1 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in CLCN1 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 17932099, 22094069, 23739125).</Comment>
